parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the instrument panel
the brakes are difficult to engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes fail to operate
the vehicle swerves or pulls to one side
the ABS system activates prematurely at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the ABS sensors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to loss of braking control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the instrument panel
the brakes are difficult to engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the ABS system activates prematurely at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of braking power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks onto electrical wiring
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes are difficult to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the four-wheel drive system to engage properly can cause loss of traction and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The four-wheel drive takes too long to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat frame can cause the seat to collapse or move unexpectedly, leading to injuries or accidents, especially in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat feels shaky or unstable
the seat back reclines unexpectedly
the seat collapses or breaks loose from the floorboard
the seat moves forward or backward while driving
the seat frame snaps or breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat track can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, leading to injuries or accidents, especially in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat moves forward or backward while driving
the seat track bolt breaks
the seat becomes loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat material can cause discomfort, distraction, or injuries while driving.
symptoms: The leather seats rip or tear
the seat material becomes worn or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, especially during heavy rain or snow, which can lead to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working unexpectedly
wipers turn on and off intermittently
wipers fail to operate when the switch is turned on
wipers make noise but do not move
poor visibility due to wiper failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle or differential can cause the vehicle to become stuck or lose control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: Clunking noise coming from the rear axle
feeling of loose gears inside the differential
rear axle locking up
audible clanking noise
vibration at speeds of 50-65 mph
heavy lateral run out
excessive tire wear.
